<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1005] GData TestDateFormater (sic) fails when the Date returned is: Sun, 23 Sep 2007 01:29:06 GMT+00:00</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1005</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;TestDateFormater.testFormatDate fails when the Date returned is Sun, 23 Sep 2007 01:29:06 GMT+00:00&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue lies with the +00:00 at the end of the string.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The question is, though, is that a valid date for GData?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is marked as major b/c it is causing nightly builds to fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
